    Don't know whether this might be false optimism, but the situation you 
describe strikes me as something that "in time ought to lead to something". 
Of course, the question is "How much time?".  But it's not something to 
become complacent about.  I. e., I trust (or hope), that you are letting it 
be known around your circle of acquaintances that you'd have no objection if 
someone wanted to pay you a salary to do something on a regular basis.

